<body>
<div class="page-title">Q2. Do you prefer travelling alone or with other people?</div>
<div class="question">Part 1 — Travel set 1</div>

<div class="feedback-card">
  <div class="legend">
    <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot dot-red"></span>빼거나 바꿀 부분</span>
    <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot dot-blue"></span>Band 9 개선 버전</span>
    <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot dot-green"></span>추가하면 좋은 내용</span>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label">✏️ 답안 + 수정 (통합)</div>
  <div class="full-text">
    I prefer traveling with others. <span class="add">(→ I generally prefer travelling with others.)</span> I <span class="wrong">expect</span> <span class="better">think</span> traveling is not just about visiting <span class="wrong">another places</span> <span class="better">new places</span>, <span class="wrong">leaving</span> <span class="better">or stepping out of your</span> comfort zone. It's also about <span class="wrong">getting to know more about yourself</span> <span class="better">getting to know yourself better</span>, which <span class="wrong">is mostly happened</span> <span class="better">tends to happen more naturally</span> <span class="wrong">when with other people</span> <span class="better">when you're around people</span>. Having said that, <span class="wrong">at the same time</span>, I think having some me time <span class="wrong">in traveling</span> <span class="better">on a trip</span> has <span class="wrong">also merits</span> <span class="better">its own value</span> <span class="wrong">in a way that in a comfort zone didn't</span> <span class="better">that group travel can't offer</span> <span class="add">— it gives you space to reflect</span>. <span class="wrong">However</span> <span class="better">So ideally</span>, <span class="wrong">the best use of resources is maybe incorporating Self-traveling into traveling with others</span> <span class="better">I'd combine the two: travel with others but carve out a bit of solo time along the way</span>.
  </div>

  <div class="section-label">📚 수정 이유 & 배울 표현</div>
  <div class="reasons">
    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">I prefer → I generally prefer</span>
      단정적인 표현보다 <strong>generally</strong>를 붙여 뉘앙스를 더하면 훨씬 세련됨. Band 9는 단호함보다 nuance를 선호.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">expect → think</span>
      expect는 "예상/기대"의 뜻이라 여기선 의미가 안 맞음. <strong>"To me, travelling is..."</strong>처럼 주어를 바꾸는 것도 좋은 대안.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">another places → new places</span>
      another는 <strong>단수 명사만</strong> 받음 (another place ✅). 복수엔 other/new.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">leaving → stepping out of</span>
      <strong>step out of your comfort zone</strong>은 원어민 고정 표현. leaving은 너무 단조로움.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">getting to know more about yourself → getting to know yourself better</span>
      <strong>get to know + 사람 + better</strong>가 훨씬 자연스러운 collocation.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">is mostly happened → happens</span>
      <strong>happen은 자동사</strong>라 수동태 불가능. 그냥 happens로.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">happens → tends to happen more naturally</span>
      <strong>tend to</strong> = "~하는 경향이 있다" — Band 9 단골 표현. 단정 대신 경향성을 표현하면 훨씬 세련됨.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">with other people → around people</span>
      <strong>be around people</strong> = "사람들 사이에 있다" — 더 원어민스러운 표현.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">"Having said that" + "at the same time" 중복</span>
      둘 다 대조·전환 표현이라 같이 쓰면 어색. 하나만!
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">in traveling → on a trip / while travelling</span>
      "여행 중"은 <strong>on a trip</strong> 또는 <strong>while travelling</strong>.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">also merits → its own merits / its own value</span>
      <strong>have its own merits/value</strong> = "나름의 가치가 있다" 관용구.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">"in a way that in a comfort zone didn't" → "that group travel can't offer"</span>
      비교 구조가 문법적으로 깨짐. <strong>that group travel can't offer</strong>로 비교 대상을 명확히.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title tip">"— it gives you space to reflect" 추가 (초록)</span>
      본문에 <strong>성찰할 공간을 준다</strong>는 구체적 이유 한 줄을 대시(—)로 덧붙이면 주장이 훨씬 설득력 있어짐. Band 9 특징 중 하나가 "주장을 구체적 근거로 뒷받침"하는 것.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">However → So ideally</span>
      However는 <strong>대조</strong>인데 여기선 결론이라 안 맞음. <strong>So ideally</strong> = "그래서 이상적으로는" — 자연스러운 결론 도입.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title err">Self-traveling → solo travel</span>
      콩글리시. 영어권에선 <strong>solo travel / travelling alone</strong>이 표준.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">the best use of resources → combine the two</span>
      "자원의 최선의 활용"은 어색. <strong>combine the two</strong>(두 가지를 결합)가 간결하고 명확.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title up">incorporating A into B → carve out time</span>
      <strong>carve out time</strong> = "(시간을) 일부러 만들어내다" — 원어민스러운 phrasal verb.
    </div>

    <div class="reason-item">
      <span class="reason-title tip">me time은 살려도 OK!</span>
      실제 영어권에서도 쓰는 표현. 이건 그대로 유지.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
